 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xerphanis>Xerphanis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 10:17:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> Well done Raz. Thoughtful and concise.<br>
<br>
As mentioned, I personally believe that your &quot;Decreased Elemental Vulnerability&quot; solution is the only one that would be in-line with the Mage class.<br>
<br>
Historically, our pets have always been considered monsters in comparison to player-characters. Presumably, the reason that this was acceptable is because Player characters can exercise better judgment, are not hindered by bad pathing, and also have significant AC advantages.<br>
<br>
In Kunark, our level 57 Earth pet easily has more hit points than a modestly equipped 57 warrior. However, this scale was reduced with the introduction of Velious and exacerbated in Luclin, where melees were given armor with incredible AC and hit points. Meanwhile, the Mage pets were not increased defensively (I say defensive because of the increased max hit cap).<br>
<br>
With the introduction of PoP, a Mage pet is now STILL only comparable to Kunark-era tanks. An increase in power should have happened for PoP-era pets, but this was not the case. As I've stated in other posts, I feel a change to increase pet hit-points by 50% is not unreasonable as well as better AC. Additionally, I'd like to see the introduction of &quot;Pet Disciplines&quot;, such as &quot;Defensive&quot; or &quot;Evasive&quot;, which can be used every 6 minutes whenever the pet is engaged.<br>
<br>
Xerphanis<br>
