<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273033">Xillion Airre</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of Felwithe, Ayonae Ro, 64 mage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.toddfederman.com/images/pet.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nemuneir>Nemuneir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 1:21:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> Azzabar said:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The solution lies in making magi pets harder to kill while they are tanking. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is the key.  Mage solo style has always differed from other solo classes drastically because we do nothing to mitigate the damage done by our prey.  Other classes kite, root, or slow, effective methods of reducing or eliminating damage done by mobs.  Mages traditionally absorb that damage on pets.<br>
<br>
This is where PoP breaks down -- mobs simply do tremendously more damage.  We can no longer absorb that damage effectively, but other solo classes are still just as good at preventing it altogether.<br>
<br>
The solution to the mage solo problem must not change the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>style</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of mage soloing, in my opinion.  We still need to absorb the damage -- if not, we're changing the fundamental idea of a solo mage.  So, I refer you back to the quote above.  We need a way to make our pets viable tanks in solo situations.<br>
<br>
Possible solution:<br>
1) As Azzabar suggested, some sort of effective slow that only work when the pet is the main tank.  I personally would lean towards a pet-only buff that is basically a damage shield, but procs a 1-tick duration slow.  Assuming the mob hits more than once per tick, and assuming the pet is the main tank,  this slow remains in effect for the entire fight.  It does not overpower mages or give them any increased group utility -- it simply allows us to use pets as tanks again.<br>
<br>
2) An improved line of pet-only hitpoint buffs and heals.  A cleric (working hard) can keep a low-end tank alive against many mobs that mages would consider soloable.  If mages had the healing abilities of a cleric (for our pets only of course) then it is feasible that we could do the same.  This line would make mages much more valuable in groups -- add a slower and DPS and you need no additional support.  The mage takes the role of two different group members.  Provided you did not want other melee in the group, mob throughput would soar.<br>
<br>
3) Improved defensive abilities of pets.  One large problem with pets tanking is that they are very bad at damage mitigation / avoidance when compared to 'real' tank.  If pets were given much better damage mitigation abilities, we could feasibly use them as our tanks for soloing.  This would also increase mage group viability similar to option #2.  Provided no other meleers were in the group, the mage can provide both DPS and tank, increasing the number of open spots for DPS or increasing the experience intake by reducing the number of groupmates.<br>
<br>
I believe option 1 is the most promising, but any are viable.<br>
<br>
